videos.description: Malik Monk finds Kentucky big man Edrice Adebayo with the alley-oop to open up the scoring for the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Adebayo puts Kentucky on the board with a big alley-oop

videos.description: Wildcats guard Malik Monk intercepts the Georgia pass and takes it down the court for the dunk.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Monk comes away with steal and a slam

videos.description: Bulldogs guard J.J. Frazier gets the transition bucket to fall as he uses the glass to pull Georgia to within six.
videos.headline: Frazier takes it coast to coast for Georgia

videos.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari discusses the Wildcats' first half against Georgia with Kaylee Hartung.
videos.headline: John Calipari halftime interview

videos.description: Wildcats guard Isaiah Briscoe finishes in the lane with the left hand, plus the foul.
videos.headline: Briscoe gets tough bucket for Kentucky

videos.description: Bam Adebayo grabs the offensive rebound and throws down the big putback slam to put the Wildcats up by 18 points.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Adebayo finishes strong with putback dunk

videos.description: Dominique Hawkins pokes the ball loose from Pape Diatta and finds Briscoe for the tough layup, plus the foul.
videos.headline: Wildcats' Hawkins finds Briscoe for the And-1 layup, plus the foul

videos.description: Kentucky guard Isaiah Briscoe talks with Kaylee Hartung after the Wildcats' 71-60 win over Georgia.
videos.headline: Briscoe: 'It's always hard to beat a team three times'
